title: Wikimedia Commons - Pictures of the Year 2007
description:
The Wikimedia Commons Picture of the Year competition is an annually organized competition in which Wikimedians from all Wikimedia projects can vote for the Picture of the Year.

2007 was the second such competition since its start in 2006. In the competition all Featured Pictures promoted in 2007 were candidates. Featured Pictures are images that the Wikimedia Commons community recognizes as of outstanding quality and value. They can be nominated by anyone, and are reviewed by the community which decides whether they are worthy of Featured Picture status.

In 2007 there were 514 images promoted to Featured Picture. The majority are photographs taken by Wikimedia editors, but there are also photographs taken by non-Wikimedians, illustrations, animations, historical photographs and drawings. 
During the first round of the competition, participants could vote for as many images they liked, resulting in 31806 votes by 665 people. The top 28 images proceeded to the final. 
In the final, 919 cast a vote, of which 84 were cast on the winner Broadway Tower in Cotswolds, England. New York City takes the second place with 67 votes. The third place is for EichhÃƒÂ¶rnchen with 66 votes.


This torrent includes the 28 pictures (in full resolution) that were selected it to the Finals.
